1
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,280
You still haven't reached her?

2
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:54,880
Yeah.

3
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,560
Her phone is unreachable.

4
00:00:58,800 --> 00:00:59,480
It's fine.

5
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:01,290
She must be with her classmates

6
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:02,400
and didn't check her phone.

7
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,680
What classmates?

8
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:04,400
I'm telling you.

9
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,240
I've noticed something off about her these past two days.

10
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:08,120
Finals.

11
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:09,280
Finals crunch.

12
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:11,240
Her state is naturally different from usual.

13
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:12,800
Can't she study at home?

14
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:14,320
I held back and didn't scold her.

15
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:15,850
At least put my mind at ease.

16
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,760
Why did you come out?

17
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,680
Have you finished your homework?

18
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,480
I'm going to the kitchen to find something to eat.

19
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,000
It's late. Don't eat.

20
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:25,280
I'm hungry.

21
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:27,620
Don't eat too much.

22
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,320
Mom.

23
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,360
My classmate's dad...

24
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:34,360
taught us how to play the ocarina.

25
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,400
I can play 'Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star' now.

26
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,680
Aunt, Mom,

27
00:01:37,759 --> 00:01:39,690
do you want me to play it for you two?

28
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:40,560
Xing,

29
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,759
it's already very late.

30
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:43,960
Let's not disturb the neighbors, okay?

31
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:46,120
Waiting for my sister together again?

32
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:46,720
By the way,

33
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,800
is it safe around here?

34
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,280
How about I go meet her at the intersection?

35
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,640
What if it's not safe coming back?

36
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,759
The security is very good here.

37
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:53,320
You can rest assured.

38
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:54,080
It's fine.

39
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,720
Someone drops my sister off every time she comes back.

40
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,280
What?

41
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,930
Nothing. I'll go back to my room to eat my sausage.

42
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,440
Mr. Yue.

43
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:12,050
This is Zhao Xiaocen's mother.

44
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,320
She said she's at Weijiayao these two days.

45
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,440
Did you know that?

46
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:16,840
Yes, I know.

47
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:18,940
It's like this.

48
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:20,800
She hasn't come home yet.

49
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,000
And I can't reach her on the phone either.

50
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,329
So I'm getting worried.

51
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:23,760
I was thinking,

52
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,960
should I go to Weijiayao to look for her?

53
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,400
Mr. Liang?

54
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,400
Okay.

55
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,560
I have the number.

56
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:33,440
Okay.

57
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,560
Goodbye.

58
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,560
Mr. Liang.

59
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,320
Sister,

60
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,520
stop calling.

61
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,640
You're making it so awkward for Xiaocen.

62
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:42,160
If something happens,

63
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,560
it won't be a matter of being awkward or not.

64
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,720
Look, it's not even 10 o'clock yet.

65
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,640
Can we just wait a little longer?

66
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,560
Let me ask her classmate.

67
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,040
Wu Jing,

68
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,440
is our Xiaocen with you?

69
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:08,080
I wonder how things are on the mountain.

70
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:09,610
Don't worry.

71
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,560
You also saw Guan Lin

72
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:14,290
fire the 'Three Rams' piece by himself last time.

73
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,060
But that wasn't Weijiayao after all.

74
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,320
Xu Xiao.

75
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,560
What if,

76
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,560
just what if,

77
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,740
he doesn't succeed this time.

78
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,680
What would the impact be?

79
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,850
Word will spread quickly in the market

80
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,280
that Guan Lin can't hold Weijiayao.

81
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,640
Then the pressure will be even greater.

82
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,880
When Master Wei made this decision,

83
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,240
he must have thought of this too.

84
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:49,800
But he also knew

85
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,180
he didn't have much time left.

86
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,180
He had to take a chance.

87
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:58,720
Now we just hope the Kiln God blesses us.

88
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,370
Xiaocen is back.

89
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,740
Xiaocen, you're back.

90
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,079
Sis, Xiaocen is back.

91
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,920
I'm sorry.

92
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,920
My phone died during the day,

93
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,120
and it shut down.

94
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:39,640
Xiaocen,

95
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,220
have you eaten?

96
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:42,920
It's hot, isn't it?

97
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,980
Summer in Jingdezhen is the hottest.

98
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,000
I made some iced mung bean soup for you.

99
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:47,680
I'll go get it for you.

100
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,940
Don't let her drink it.

101
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,520
Qingying.

102
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,480
Go back to your room first.

103
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,610
I need to talk to her.

104
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,720
It's fine. I'll just stay here. Go ahead.

105
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,180
Go back to your room first.

106
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,040
Okay, okay.

107
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,770
How was I supposed to know your phone was dead?

108
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,680
I couldn't reach you.

109
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,160
If something happened to you,

110
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,200
do you know how worried I would be?

111
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,120
Mom, I'm sorry.

112
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,960
I will never do this again.

113
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:42,690
Never again?

114
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,480
How many times have you come home late recently?

115
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,520
How many times recently

116
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:48,250
have I not known where you were?

117
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,240
Zhao Xiaocen.

118
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,120
Before this semester ends,

119
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,880
other than going to class,

120
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,480
no matter where you go,

121
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,159
you must tell me first.

122
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,560
Otherwise, you're not going anywhere.

123
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:02,760
Got it?

124
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,240
I got it.

125
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,360
The wind has died down.

126
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,720
The temperature inside has dropped too.

127
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,650
Go back and rest.

128
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,130
Go back, go back.

129
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:14,600
Okay.

130
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:15,800
Go back.

131
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,330
Master Guan.

132
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,730
It's your turn to sit in this chair now.

133
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,080
Go back.

134
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,250
Go get some rest.

135
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,680
Wet wood and dry wood

136
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,800
must never be burned together.

137
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,480
Only if you fire it correctly

138
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,480
can the porcelain

139
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:41,720
be as green as jade, as clear as a mirror,

140
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,200
as thin as paper, and sound like a chime.

141
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,040
As for porcelain,

142
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,480
its unique charm

143
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:50,480
lies in clay, kiln, fire, and wood

144
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,490
and their delicate relationship.

145
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,800
And the kiln master

146
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,760
is the one who adjusts this balance.

147
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:17,900
That's enough.

148
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,560
Stop adding firewood.

149
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:21,820
Put it down.

150
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,640
I tell you,

151
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,690
after sealing the door,

152
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:29,720
you shouldn't add too much firewood.

153
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,810
At this point, you have to rely on your eyes

154
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,080
and your ears.

155
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,200
Controlling the heat

156
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,400
must be like cooking porridge over a slow fire.

157
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:43,930
Slow fire and fine work allow the glaze to penetrate deeply.

158
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,440
Never rush.

159
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,000
You need to be patient.

160
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:51,280
The temperature shouldn't rise too fast.

161
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:52,240
Got it?

162
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:48,410
Let's go.

163
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,040
Rest assured.

164
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,000
As for Mr. Wei,

165
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:14,060
I've hired a professional caregiver to look after him.

166
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,970
But what about you guys?

167
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,960
It's already the end of the term.

168
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,720
You have to review and take exams for every course.

169
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,200
So you should focus

170
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,820
your minds back on school.

171
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:25,240
Okay.

172
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,200
Mr. Wei hasn't woken up yet.

173
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,200
But the doctor said there's no rush,

174
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,530
and he's stable for now.

175
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,450
Let's come see him another day.

176
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,360
How are things at Weijiayao?

177
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,600
Brother Guan Lin is keeping watch.

178
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,330
I hope the kiln opens smoothly.

179
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:40,520
I also hope

180
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:42,800
Mr. Wei wakes up soon.

181
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,660
Like stacking blocks.

182
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:58,290
Stack them into the shape of the kiln opening.

183
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:05,300
Add them in.

184
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:05,760
Okay.

185
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:09,410
Xiaocen.

186
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:10,800
Manual labor is too tough.

187
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,600
You don't need to do it.

188
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,200
It's fine.

189
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,840
I want to help too.

190
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,250
Then be careful.

191
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:44,640
Let me.

192
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,720
Guan Lin is much steadier now.

193
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:53,250
He's getting more and more of Mr. Wei's style.

194
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,040
Masters.

195
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,920
Xiaocen, Xu Xiao,

196
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,090
let's go eat.

197
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,120
Go ahead.

198
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,840
Okay.

199
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,280
Good work.

200
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:05,320
Good work.

201
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:05,960
Go ahead.

202
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,020
Let's go, Xiaocen.

203
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,040
Go on.

204
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:17,880
Xu Xiao.

205
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,040
Xu Xiao.

206
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:28,680
Xiaocen.

207
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,170
Xiaocen.

208
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,010
Xiaocen.

209
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:33,170
Xiaocen.

210
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,200
Xiaocen, wake up.

211
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:51,560
Ma'am.

212
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,240
Cencen.

213
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:06,580
Cencen, what happened to you?

214
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,130
Ma'am, don't worry.

215
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,280
She just fell asleep after taking her medicine.

216
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:13,540
The doctor said it's chronic urticaria.

217
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,320
Ma'am.

218
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:56,640
My name is Xu Xiao.

219
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,780
I'm Xiaocen's classmate.

220
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,760
I just went through her phone

221
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:03,020
and found your number.

222
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,280
Ma'am, I'm sorry.

223
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:09,660
I was careless.

224
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:10,840
I noticed earlier

225
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,040
that Xiaocen had red bumps on her body.

226
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,200
I thought it was just from the summer heat and humidity.

227
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:13,960
Do you think

228
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,160
you're a doctor?

229
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,120
Do you know what hives are,

230
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,400
and what causes them?

231
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,120
Lack of sleep,

232
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,040
extreme fatigue, and mental stress

233
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,520
will all worsen her allergies.

234
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,080
There are also external factors.

235
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,920
Weather, food, dust,

236
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,040
and UV rays

237
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,730
will make it even worse.

238
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,370
The red spots on her body

239
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,560
are caused by vasodilation,

240
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,960
and can also cause edema.

241
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,320
Luckily, it was only on her skin this time.

242
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,560
If it had occurred in her throat,

243
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,520
you know it could have suffocated her.

244
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,580
Do you understand?

245
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:49,560
I'm sorry.

246
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:51,960
It's all my fault.

247
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:54,960
Okay.

248
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:58,440
Let me ask you something.

249
00:13:58,680 --> 00:13:59,680
Are you currently

250
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,330
getting very close to our Xiaocen?

251
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:09,580
Auntie,

252
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,580
I like Xiaocen.

253
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,320
I am serious about her.

254
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,400
Do you know that saying this

255
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:15,440
means you have to take responsibility?

256
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:15,960
I know.

257
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,050
What do you know?

258
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,400
Do you really understand Xiaocen?

259
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,000
Do you know about our family?

260
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,690
How long have you known her?

261
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,960
Now you have her leaving early and coming home late,

262
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,280
not even resting on weekends.

263
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,200
Last time, she was bedridden with stomach pain.

264
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,260
And now, she ended up in the hospital.

265
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,920
Is this how you show you're serious?

266
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:37,980
Auntie, I'm sorry.

267
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,440
I promise

268
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,760
this will never happen again.

269
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:43,220
I will definitely take good care of Xiaocen.

270
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,420
Where are you from?

271
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:46,930
Jingdezhen.

272
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,720
What about your parents?

273
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:51,970
Here too.

274
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,160
So,

275
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,960
you were born in Jingdezhen,

276
00:14:58,640 --> 00:14:59,760
went to college here,

277
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:00,760
and in the future,

278
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,400
you won't leave Jingdezhen. Is that right?

279
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,930
Then how will you take care of Xiaocen?

280
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,410
Walking her home

281
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,680
is considered taking care of her?

282
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:24,480
After Xiaocen

283
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,300
finishes her studies,

284
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,020
I will take her away from here.

285
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,400
I will absolutely not leave her in Jingdezhen.

286
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:11,760
Guan,

287
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:12,760
hurry up and eat.

288
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,320
First, filling. Second, firing. Third, cooling.

289
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,080
Master said

290
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,880
the three most important things in kiln firing

291
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,480
are filling the kiln, controlling the heat,

292
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:20,160
and the proper time to cool down.

293
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,840
It looks like the kiln needs to be cooled down soon.

294
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,600
But you still have to eat.

295
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,600
You guys go ahead.

296
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:36,840
Xiaocen,

297
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:40,840
you're awake.

298
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:43,210
Are you feeling any better?

299
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:44,880
Mom,

300
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,080
why are you here?

301
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:48,880
Why am I here?

302
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,920
Look at all the rashes on your hands.

303
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,250
You didn't even tell me.

304
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,240
Don't move. Lie down.

305
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:57,080
Get some rest.

306
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:00,760
Xu Xiao,

307
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,720
who told you to come?

308
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:12,000
Uh, the hospital called me.

309
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,119
Let me see what kind of medicine this is.

310
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,319
You're back.

311
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:22,960
Xiaocen,

312
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:24,079
how are you doing?

313
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:24,480
Aunt,

314
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,200
what did the doctor say?

315
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,280
I'm fine, Aunt.

316
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,500
Look, my rash went away on its own.

317
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,000
The doctor said I'm fine.

318
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,080
Look at you.

319
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,800
How could you be so careless?

320
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,260
You must be careful from now on, you know?

321
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:43,200
Master.

322
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:47,080
The fire at Weijiayao is out.

323
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,840
Don't you want to see if I won

324
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:51,210
or lost this battle?

325
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,920
If the firing went bad,

326
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,520
get up and scold me.

327
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:08,640
Master!

328
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,240
Doctor!

329
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:12,720
Doctor!

330
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,240
Doctor!

331
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,200
Cencen.

332
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:21,250
Here,

333
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,760
take the medicine the doctor prescribed.

334
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,280
Okay.

335
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:26,840
Here.

336
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,810
Slow down, don't choke.

337
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:34,400
How is it?

338
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,050
Feeling better?

339
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,880
Much better.

340
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:41,490
That's good.

341
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:45,240
I want to go back to school in a couple of days.

342
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,770
Because I still have exams.

343
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:51,920
Mom,

344
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,040
I

345
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:56,320
promise

346
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:58,320
this won't happen again.

347
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,840
I'll take good care of my body.

348
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:04,120
Cencen,

349
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:08,040
Mom wants to apologize to you first.

350
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,080
Having you choose this major back then,

351
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:11,520
firstly,

352
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:14,040
was considering your Aunt is right in Jingdezhen.

353
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:14,720
Secondly,

354
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,090
it's because for a girl,

355
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,480
if you choose this major,

356
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,240
you can work in a museum in the future.

357
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,640
It's a state-owned unit,

358
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,610
and a clerical job is quite stable.

359
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:24,280
But to be honest,

360
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,680
I really didn't expect this major

361
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,770
would drain so much of your energy.

362
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:32,960
It was poorly considered on my part.

363
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,160
Mom,

364
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,020
what are you trying to say?

365
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:47,010
I've already asked around.

366
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,560
After your freshman year,

367
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,400
you can switch majors.

368
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,720
I want to discuss it with the school

369
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:54,920
and have you transferred to museology.

370
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:57,880
Mom, look,

371
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,300
I've already studied for a semester,

372
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,800
and I have so many friends.

373
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,280
I don't want to switch majors.

374
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:10,200
You have four years of college.

375
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:12,520
You'll have plenty of chances

376
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,050
to make new friends, right?

377
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:15,960
Then I think

378
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:17,760
you should discuss this with me.

379
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,880
Aren't I discussing it with you now?

380
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,920
This isn't a discussion.

381
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,140
You're just informing me.

382
00:20:27,920 --> 00:20:28,520
You kid,

383
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:30,250
how can you talk to me like this?

384
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,000
Do you know how serious

385
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,200
your hives were this time?

386
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,480
If something went wrong,

387
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,140
who would you be letting down?

388
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,920
This time was just an accident.

389
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:40,520
It seems

390
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,800
it has nothing to do with my major, right?

391
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,160
How does it have nothing to do with it?

392
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,220
If you hadn't gone to that Weijiayao,

393
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,920
if you weren't overly exhausted,

394
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,580
this wouldn't have happened.

395
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,320
I'm telling you,

396
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:51,960
you're irresponsible with your own body,

397
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,820
so I have to be responsible for it.

398
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:55,400
Mom,

399
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:58,720
I really like this major.

400
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,560
I promise you,

401
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,640
this won't happen again.

402
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,400
Your dad and I have already discussed it.

403
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,240
We've decided to change your major.

404
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,360
Then what did you say you were discussing with me?

405
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:09,290
I am your mother.

406
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:11,680
You have to listen to whatever I say.

407
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:17,480
Yes.

408
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,920
I must listen to you.

409
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,720
I've had to listen to you since I was a child.

410
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:29,720
What's wrong?

411
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:31,000
Why so loud?

412
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,640
What's going on with you two?

413
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,080
Qingfang, what's wrong?

414
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:35,200
Okay.

415
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:39,400
Are you crying,

416
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:40,840
Xiaocen?

417
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,400
Don't cry.

418
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:48,850
Don't cry, Xiaocen.

419
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,760
I haven't finished watching.

420
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:03,490
Why did you change the channel?

421
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,360
Hurry up.

422
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:11,900
Stop watching.

423
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,210
It's so late.

424
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,760
Put this on the table.

425
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,400
No playing, understand?

426
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:18,920
Got it.

427
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:19,900
Go to sleep now.

428
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,340
Just say what you want.

429
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,040
Why are you looking at me?

430
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:45,800
Qingfang,

431
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:48,080
are you

432
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:49,880
really going to change Xiaocen's major?

433
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:50,400
Yes.

434
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,160
I'm not making this decision out of anger.

435
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,640
Her father and I have already discussed it.

436
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:59,520
She shouldn't have chosen this major in the first place.

437
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,800
Who knew this major would be so exhausting?

438
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,400
How could her health be good?

439
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:07,920
Xiaocen's allergy this time was just an accident.

440
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:08,840
Aren't you

441
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:11,040
making a mountain out of a molehill?

442
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:12,720
What if

443
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,880
you change her major,

444
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:15,480
and she

445
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:17,200
is still unhappy there?

446
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:19,040
Then she just won't work.

447
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,280
I'll support her for the rest of her life.

448
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:20,840
So what?

449
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:22,880
Can't I support my own daughter?

450
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:28,040
Don't you think

451
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,560
Xiaocen is very happy every day

452
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:31,960
in her current major?

453
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:34,280
She can't risk her life just to be happy.

454
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:35,920
It's not that serious.

455
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,080
It is that serious.

456
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:42,720
It's not like you don't know.

457
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,450
I've already made a mistake

458
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:46,840
with Xiaocen,

459
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,440
and I can't make a second one.

460
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:52,920
This child

461
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,640
has always been prone to allergies since she was little.

462
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:56,880
I was very careful.

463
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,000
But that one time,

464
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,840
I worked overtime and came home late.

465
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,700
She ate the shrimp from the fridge

466
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,000
and stayed in that hospital

467
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,400
for a whole month.

468
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:06,600
How can I not worry?

469
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,680
Isn't that from a long time ago?

470
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,060
Xiaocen is doing fine now, isn't she?

471
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,160
Besides,

472
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:18,240
making her change majors

473
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,860
isn't just because of her health, right?

474
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,480
I heard from Xing

475
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:25,320
that a boy often walks her home,

476
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:26,280
right?

477
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:29,200
Then tell me, am I wrong to intervene?

478
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,680
Xiaocen is old enough.

479
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,400
It's normal for her to date.

480
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,120
You also dated at Xiaocen's age.

481
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,450
And what was the result?

482
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:38,560
So,

483
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,320
don't try to persuade me.

484
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:41,160
I've already decided.
